title: For Sale:  Original Pre-Ban Hk-91
postcontent: Once again, I've decided to make some room in my collection, so I'm parting with one of my remaining Hk-91 rifles.Manufactured by Heckler and Koch in 1981 ('IB' coded receiver), this is the semi-automatic version of the G3 rifle. Chambered for 7.62x51 NATO (.308). Those of you who are familiar with the Hk-91 already know that the manufacturing quality, reliability, and accuracy of these German-produced rifles is unmatched. A ban on the import of these rifles took effect in 1989, so whatever made it into the U.S. prior to that is what's available on the market. This is one of the 48,817 Hk-91 rifles that were imported from 1974 - 1989.This one is in outstanding condition. The previous owner had only put a minimal number of rounds through the rifle, so when I purchased it approximately six months ago, my intent was to keep it as a safe queen.For personal preference, I decided to send the rifle out to Jayson Cotter (IGF) to have him remove the blue-gray finish which was worn in a few places, apply a manganese-phosphate parkerizing, and then complete the work with a matte black 'Envirotech' finish over this. As you can see, the finish is flawless.The bore and chamber are mirror-bright and in excellent condition as you'd expect. The muzzle end of the barrel is threaded to accept the flash hider or other accessories (note that the factory flash hider's innovative locking design permits it to be installed / removed by hand and does not require any tools). The bolt carrier and bolt head are 'IB' coded.The furniture is German Army surplus, taken directly from a G3 service rifle. It matches nicely and looks menacing on this Hk-91! Definitely something that will turn heads if you decide to take this out to the range! If you really want to take this rifle to the next level, the receiver is factory-designed to accept a Hensoldt Wetzlar 4x24 scope and claw mount.Included with the rifle are three G3 magazines (two of which are unissued, new-in-wrap), an original G3 canvas sling, and an original cover for the flash hider to keep dirt and debris out of the bore when you're trekking across the African savanna.Asking $2000 shipped for the lot. First "I'll take it" claims it! Not interested in any trades..Also, Comes with two Buffers. The 'standard' buffer is already installed and an unissued G3 heavy buffer is included.
